  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your casserole dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with foil</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-creamy-lean-pork-ragu-and-spaghetti/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based, <strong>hob-safe oven-proof casserole dish </strong>with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>lean pork mince </strong>(remove the paper if required!)<strong> </strong>and your <strong>dried</strong> <strong>oregano </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until beginning to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-creamy-lean-pork-ragu-and-spaghetti/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and grate your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Top, tail and grate your <strong>carrot[s]</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-creamy-lean-pork-ragu-and-spaghetti/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the pork is starting to brown, add the <strong>grated carrot</strong>, <strong>grated onion </strong>and your <strong>roasted garlic paste </strong>and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-creamy-lean-pork-ragu-and-spaghetti/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong>, <strong>Chinese rice wine </strong>and 600ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [800ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[1L] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Break your <strong>spaghetti</strong> in half and add it to the dish, give everything a good mix up to separate the strands</p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat, season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong>, then cover with a lid and put the dish in the oven for an initial 25 min or until the spaghetti is tender and the pork is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-creamy-lean-pork-ragu-and-spaghetti/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-creamy-lean-pork-ragu-and-spaghetti/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the spaghetti is tender, remove the dish from the oven and add your <strong>soft cheese</strong>, <strong>half </strong>your <strong>Italian hard cheese </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>,<strong> </strong>then give everything a good mix up</p><p>Return the dish to the oven and cook, covered, for a final 5 min – this is your <strong>one pot creamy lean pork ragù and spaghetti</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of water if the pasta is looking a little dry!</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-creamy-lean-pork-ragu-and-spaghetti/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>one pot creamy lean pork ragù and spaghetti </strong>and sprinkle with the <strong>remaining Italian hard cheese </strong>and a generous grind of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>basil</strong> roughly over the top with<strong> </strong>scissors</p><p>Dig in!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
